parameters: \nc<>So, with that, we welcome Kei's enrollment! Yay!

\nc<>With this, Kei-san is now an official believer of the
Paradise Religion!

\nc<>...However, as a regular believer, they mainly use the basic
facilities and engage in conversations.

\nc<>On top of that, there are saints, apostles, and the
founder, right? What kind of facilities do the saints use?

\nc<>W-Well, actually, I don't know much either. Hehe... I've
been just a regular believer all this time too.

\nc<>I've been trying to become a saint for a while now, you
know.

\nc<>I see. So that's why they were doing missionary work on the
roadside.

\nc<>Yes! In order to become a saint, contribution points are
necessary. These activities are meant to increase
contribution points.

\nc<>(It's unusual. It's natural for the scores of evangelism and
donations to be high, but) (Meditation is strangely high
too... Other than that, they're mostly low.)
\nc<>Can't you become an apostle with contribution points?

\nc<>Yes. I heard that apostles require significant
achievements... or something like that.
\nc<>Is it okay if I bring a lot of people?

\nc<>(They must be active as villains.) (Their contribution
points are also set to be high.)

\nc<>A-Actually, the reason I tried to become a saint is because
most kids my age are on that side.

\nc<>But since Kei-san joined, it might not be bad to be with
Kei-san... hehe...
\nc<>So, what do you want to do, Kei-san?

\nc<>(Setting aside villainous activities,) (It is efficient to
aim for evangelism and meditation in order to become a
saint.)

\nc<>(But, setting aside the former, the latter seems
suspicious.)

\nc<>(Here... for now, let's wait for an opportunity while
engaging in different activities.)
\nc<>Today is the first day, so maybe volunteering is enough.

\nc<>Is that so? Th-then I will join as well. I will guide you,
so come this way!
\nc<>I-I didn't do it this time, but...

\nc<>Meditation can be done later, so please feel free to join
whenever you like!

\nc<>(I'm sorry, Yukiko, but that meditation seems too
suspicious.)
\nc<>Let's go here safely, even if it takes a little time.
